Arthur Henry Kenney (c.1776–1855)  was an Irish priest who was Dean of Achonry from 1812 to 1821.He was educated at Trinity College Dublin, where he was elected a Scholar. He was the incumbent at Kilmacrennan before his years as Dean; and Rector of St Olave, Southwark afterwards.
He died in Boulogne on 27 January 1855.
